5:
Huh. So that's why you asked for me
out of the blue.
8:
You want solid proof that FQPress is
up to no good, and you want my
help to get it.
10:
The plan is to take them in on
suspicion of obstructing PBC's
business with slander.
13:
Then catch them for the other stuff
while we're at it... Are you sure this is
legal?
16:
My dear boy... Businesses define the
law, and we are the ones who judge
those businesses.
18:
In other words, we're as shady and
underhanded as everyone else.
24:
Enough with the idiotic jokes.
I'm sorry, Alk, but this matter involves
you and yours.
27:
Everything started with Noxel Group
and that hole in the sky.
30:
When the Myriad Project was
suspended and repairs began,
many higher-ups were forced from
their positionsâ€”some violently.
37:
Behind closed doors, an outright war
began for the empty seats, and
FQPress was no innocent bystander.
40:
Now... Who was it that incited the
freedom blaster in the first place?
43:
There's also the problem of what
FQPress has been circulating
around the black market.
45:
Genome Soldiers. Blueprints for
those have been serving as the
basis for biomutants. Sound familiar?
53:
A suitable amount of capital per
person.
57:
Yes, I'm asking for a team. I know
what you lot are capable of when
you work together.
62:
Yep, that there's what we call
freedom of the press.
63:
We just take what we see on social
media and put it into articles.
Anything you read is just your
average person's opinion.
65:
If you're gonna try and censor us
anyway, then you're asking for a war.
68:
Bold words coming from the person
manipulating those opinions.
71:
There's no hiding from us. We traced
the information to accounts that
you bought followers for.
75:
Ooh, scary. You're really gunning for
my arrest.
77:
Or perhaps... you're trying to get me
for something else?
79:
Now, now... You know our contract
doesn't allow for arrests on separate
charges. Are you gonna make me
call the authorities?
82:
You're deluded by pride and power.
Is this what greed does to a man?
85:
I wonder if you can afford to be so
lax. Haven't you noticed? We've
already infiltrated your secret server.
90:
Hiyah! Before you stands Zantetsu,
ninja samurai and warrior of justice!
95:
Lord Alk, we hit the treasure trove!
Secret communication logs with the
Star Augurs and money transfer
data secured!
98:
WHAT?! Do you have any idea how
much I paid for that security?!
100:
Sorry to burst your bubble, but I
created that exact firewall for
homework when I was five years old.
104:
There were a few minor changes, of
course, but nothing I couldn't handle.
107:
Honestly, those changes made the
code worse, not better. But hey, I
think a bad boss man deserves a
bad coder.
112:
There you have it. Will you come
quietly or make this more difficult
than it has to be?
115:
...What, you think I'm going to just roll
over and take it?
123: Rgh... All right, all right! You got me!
124:
What is it you want? Money? Access
to the Myriad Project?
126:
You and Lunus are in trouble right
now, yeah? I could edit the sales
data and make your value go up
tenfold!
128:
...You really are obsessed with
nothing but money and power.
132:
Is that what you think? You of all
people should understand.
133:
I'm just giving the brainless masses
what they want!
136:
They'll take whatever justice they
can get, no matter how many lives
get ruined because of it!
138:
Isn't that why you did what you did?
It was to appease them!
144:
Once upon a time, I truly believed it
was the duty of the strong to carry
the weight of the weak.
148:
That my job was to uphold justice
and punish evil. But a certain person
showed me I was wrong.
150:
She taught me that anyone, weak or
strong, is capable of shining that
brightly...
152:
I'm curious. Why did you start
FQPress?
155:
To earn more money than anyone
else. That's why I tried to claw my
way to the top.
158:
But why desire money to that
degree? What use do you have for
that much?
161:
It's fine if you don't have an answer
yet.
164:
You'll have plenty of time to think up
something from behind bars.
168:
I remember you wrote an article on
me, back when you were still a
journalist.
170:
Called me a demon hell-bent on
revengeâ€”an unworthy successor of
my master.
173:
Looking back on it now, you did well
to notice my crumbling mental
state before I did.
176:
I just thought I'd mention it. Do with
this information what you will.
179:
Didn't take you for the
spouting-nonsense type... But I'll
keep it in my mind.
186:
I tried my best to imitate her. Laugh
at me if you wish. Just don't give me
that look.
189:
I won't laugh at you for trying to do a
good thing.
193: I can't walk the same path as her.
196:
But at the very least, I'll try to see the
world as she does.
